  "prompt": "What would happen if a foreigner child's parents died during a trip to the US, and the child had no one to look after him back home?",
  "response": "In such a scenario, several things could happen depending on specific circumstances:\n\n1. Child Protective Services would likely get involved\n2. The child would be temporarily placed in foster care or a temporary guardian\n3. The US government would work to contact the child's nearest relatives\n4. If no relatives could be found, the consulate of the child's home country would be notified\n5. Efforts would be made to either:\n- Locate and bring relatives to the US\n- Arrange for the child to be returned to their home country\n- Find a long-term guardian or adoptive family\n\nThe specific process would depend on immigration status, bilateral agreements between countries, and the individual child's circumstances.",
